=== 用户规模和产品更新 ===
2015年6月30日，苹果公司正式发布了{{lang|en|Apple Music}}。7月初，苹果移动设备用户中已经有38%升级至支持{{lang|en|Apple Music}}服务的最新操作系统{{lang|en|iOS}} 8.4。商业分析公司{{le|Mixpanel|Mixpanel}}指出，这意味着已经有上亿用户能够有机会体验{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的免费试用。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://venturebeat.com/2015/07/06/watch-out-spotify-38-of-apple-mobile-devices-now-running-ios-8-4-with-apple-music-new-data-shows/|title=Watch out, Spotify: 38% of Apple mobile devices now running iOS 8.4 with Apple Music, new data shows|work=Venture Beat|date=2015-07-06|accessdate=2015-07-19|first=Jordan|last=Novet|archive-date=2015-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150928122218/http://venturebeat.com/2015/07/06/watch-out-spotify-38-of-apple-mobile-devices-now-running-ios-8-4-with-apple-music-new-data-shows/|dead-url=no}}</ref>到2015年10月时，{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的用户数已经超过1,500万，其中650万用户为付费用户，其他用户仍在三个月的免费试用期内。付费用户人数是同类型音乐流媒体服务巨头{{lang|en|[[Spotify|Spotify]]}}的三分之一。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/10/20/9572667/apple-music-subscriber-count-number-paid|title=Apple Music has a third as many paying subscribers as Spotify|work=The Verge|date=2015-10-20|accessdate=2015-11-11|first=Sam|last=Byford|archive-date=2017-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120025544/http://www.theverge.com/2015/10/20/9572667/apple-music-subscriber-count-number-paid|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/10/20/us-apple-ceo-music-idUSKCN0SE09S20151020|title=Apple Music hits 6.5 million paid users: Tim Cook|work=Reuters|date=2015-10-20|accessdate=2015-11-11|first=Julia|last=Love|archive-date=2015-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023014003/http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/10/20/us-apple-ceo-music-idUSKCN0SE09S20151020|dead-url=no}}</ref>数百万用户在试用期结束后没有继续付费使用这项服务，但苹果公司首席执行官[[蒂姆·库克|蒂姆·库克]]仍然对这一数据表示满意。美国投资公司{{le|FBR资本市场|FBR Capital Markets}}分析人士丹尼尔·艾夫斯（{{lang|en|Daniel Ives}}）也认为这一数据好于预期，他认为按照这一发展速度，{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的付费用户在12个月后将可能达到2,000万。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-et-ct-apple-music-subscribers-spotify-20151021-story.html|title=Apple Music hits a 'triple' with 6.5 million paying subscribers, analyst says|work=Los Angeles Times|date=2015-10-21|accessdate=2015-11-11|first=Ryan|last=Faughnder|archive-date=2015-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151111052825/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-et-ct-apple-music-subscribers-spotify-20151021-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2015/10/19/apples-tim-cook-speaks/74251796/|title=Apple lost millions of Music users when trial ended; 6.5M remain|work=USA Today|date=2015-10-20|accessdate=2015-11-11|first=Jefferson|last=Graham|archive-date=2015-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151110172658/http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2015/10/19/apples-tim-cook-speaks/74251796/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

截至2016年1月，苹果的音乐流媒体服务Apple Music已经拥有超过1000万付费用户，仅用了半年时间就达到了一个新里程碑。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tech.qq.com/a/20160111/007332.htm|title=Apple Music上线半年付费用户超1000万|work=腾讯科技|date=2016-01-11|accessdate=2016-01-11|archive-date=2016-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160125234127/http://tech.qq.com/a/20160111/007332.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url = http://www.theverge.com/2016/1/10/10745630/apple-music-total-paid-subscribers-vs-spotify|title = Apple Music reportedly approaches half as many paid subscribers as Spotify|last = D'Orazio|first = Dante|date = 2016-01-10|work = The Verge|accessdate = 2016-02-05|archive-date = 2016-02-05|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160205101806/http://www.theverge.com/2016/1/10/10745630/apple-music-total-paid-subscribers-vs-spotify|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/742955d2-b79b-11e5-bf7e-8a339b6f2164.html|title = Apple’s music streaming subscribers top 10m|last = Garrahan|first = Matthew|date = 2016-01-10|work = Financial Times|accessdate = 2016-02-05|last2 = Bradshaw|first2 = Tim|archive-date = 2016-02-02|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160202093656/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0%2F742955d2-b79b-11e5-bf7e-8a339b6f2164.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>这一数据已经接近{{Lang|en|Spotify}}付费用户数的二分之一，使{{Lang|en|Apple Music}}成为全球流媒体音乐市场的第二大服务。<ref name=":0" />2016年6月的[[全球軟件開發者年會|全球软件开发者年会]]上，苹果公司宣布{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的付费用户已经超过1500万；同时还宣布已重新设计{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的操作界面，将于同年秋季与{{Lang|en|iOS 10}}共同发布。<ref name=":4" />

== 评价和反响 ==
在{{lang|en|Apple Music}}正式宣布推出之前，美国科技新闻网站{{lang|en|[[The_Verge|The Verge]]}}评论担心此项服务和已有的类似服务相比没有独特之处，歌曲库大小与已有的服务相似，价格也并没有优势<ref name="Verge: announce"/>。{{lang|en|The Verge}}撰稿人尼雷·帕特尔（{{lang|en|Nilay Patel}}）更是抱怨称各家音乐流媒体服务之间相互争夺市场份额反而给用户带来不便。他称{{lang|en|[[Spotify|Spotify]]}}、{{lang|en|[[亞馬遜公司|Amazon Prime]]}}、[[Google_Play_音乐|Google Play 音乐]]和{{lang|en|Apple Music}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=AirPods Max， AirPods 不支持苹果「无损」音乐服务 |url=https://magicmachines.io/airpods-max-and-airpods-apple-music-lossless-compatibility/ |access-date=2021-05-18 |archive-date=2021-05-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210519035710/https://magicmachines.io/airpods-max-and-airpods-apple-music-lossless-compatibility }}</ref>都有各自的“独家内容”和价格，之间缺乏兼容性，使用户无从下手。<ref name="Verge: lock-in">{{cite web |url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/6/5/8737537/apple-music-and-the-terrible-return-of-drm |accessdate=2015-07-19 |title=Apple Music and the terrible return of DRM |last1=Patel |first1=Nilay |date=2015-06-05 |work=[[The_Verge|The Verge]] |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Z8fOF8iu?url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/6/5/8737537/apple-music-and-the-terrible-return-of-drm |archivedate=2015-06-08 |deadurl=no }}</ref>服务正式发布后，{{lang|en|Apple Music}}也因操作复杂、故障不断而遭到了大量用户的指责。《[[国际财经时报|国际财经时报]]》撰稿人马克斯·维伦斯（{{lang|en|Max Willens}}）称这是苹果公司发布过的“最复杂的产品”，服务中加入了太多功能，用户友好度不足，给大量不熟悉流媒体理念和操作的用户带来麻烦。整个{{lang|en|Apple Music}}服务仍存在诸多设计不完善之处，时而出现的程序错误也引发用户不满。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/apple-music-full-design-flaws-are-driving-users-experts-nuts-1990340|title=Apple Music Is Full Of Design Flaws That Are Driving Users And Experts Nuts|work=International Business Times|date=2015-06-30|accessdate=2015-07-19|first=Max|last=Willen|archive-date=2015-07-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721235224/http://www.ibtimes.com/apple-music-full-design-flaws-are-driving-users-experts-nuts-1990340|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Verge: review">{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/7/8/8911731/apple-music-review|title=Apple Music review|work=[[The_Verge|The Verge]]|date=2015-07-08|accessdate=2015-07-19|first=Micah|last=Singleton|archive-date=2015-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150717065231/http://www.theverge.com/2015/7/8/8911731/apple-music-review|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2016/5/13/11674388/apple-music-itunes-file-deletion-bug-update|title=Apple says it doesn't know why iTunes users are losing their music files|accessdate=2016-06-14|author=|date=2016-05-13|last=Statt|first=Nick|publisher=The Verge|archive-date=2016-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610194517/http://www.theverge.com/2016/5/13/11674388/apple-music-itunes-file-deletion-bug-update|dead-url=no}}</ref>

然而整体上，媒体和用户还是对{{lang|en|Apple Music}}给出了正面的评价。{{lang|en|The Verge}}撰稿人迪特尔·约翰（{{lang|en|Dieter John}}）称{{lang|en|Apple Music}}虽然有一些小问题，但已经满足了人们对流媒体服务的所有需求<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/6/30/8869347/apple-music-first-impressions-hands-on-video|title=Apple Music first impressions: something borrowed, something new|accessdate=2015-07-19|date=2015-06-30|last=Bohn|first=Dieter|work=The Verge|archive-date=2015-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150717073940/http://www.theverge.com/2015/6/30/8869347/apple-music-first-impressions-hands-on-video|dead-url=no}}</ref>。{{lang|en|The Verge}}另一位撰稿人米卡·辛格顿（{{lang|en|Micah Singleton}}）指出，当前{{lang|en|Apple Music}}存在的问题都是可以及时修正的，这项服务整体来讲十分优秀，将会推动音乐产业进入全新的未来。他认为“{{lang|en|Beats 1}}”是整个服务中最惊喜的部分，称三位{{lang|en|DJ}}挑选的音乐胜过其他的流媒体服务。辛格顿还认为“为你推荐”部分是{{lang|en|Apple Music}}与其他流媒体服务相比最大的优势。<ref name="Verge: review"/>新闻网站{{lang|en|[[Mashable|Mashable]]}}撰稿人克里斯蒂娜·华伦（{{lang|en|Christina Warren}}）认为，{{lang|en|Apple Music}}更加重视“人”的作用，尤其赞赏了其多种多样的网络电台以及“为你推荐”部分的准确推荐。她认为“为你推荐”部分是{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的真正核心内容。<ref>{{cite web|last1=Warren|first1=Christina|title=Apple Music first look: It's all about curation, curation, curation|url=http://mashable.com/2015/06/30/apple-music-hands-on/|website=Mashable|publisher=Mashable, Inc.|7=|date=2015-06-30|accessdate=2015-07-19|archive-date=2015-07-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721173406/http://mashable.com/2015/06/30/apple-music-hands-on/|dead-url=no}}</ref>技术新闻网站{{lang|en|[[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]]}}则赞赏了{{lang|en|Connect}}平台，认为苹果公司强调未签约的独立艺人也可以使用这一平台，重新证明了苹果公司在2000年代中期曾经“敢于尝鲜”的勇气<ref name="Ars: next chapter"/>。总体而言，{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的推荐播放列表和{{lang|en|Beats 1}}电台获得了广泛赞誉，而{{lang|en|Connect}}平台的反响则相对冷淡，未能吸引用户的关注<ref>{{cite web|title=Apple Music Is Now Courting Fashion Lovers With Playlists Curated By Designers|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2016/06/08/apple-music-is-now-courting-fashion-lovers-with-playlists-curated-by-designers/|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=2016-07-16|date=2016-06-08|archive-date=2016-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719234430/http://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2016/06/08/apple-music-is-now-courting-fashion-lovers-with-playlists-curated-by-designers/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Future For Apple Music's Social Feature 'Connect' Doesn't Look Bright|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2016/05/12/the-future-for-apple-musics-social-feature-connect-doesnt-look-bright/#6f816105542a|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=2016-07-16|date=2016-05-12|archive-date=2016-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160720094031/http://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2016/05/12/the-future-for-apple-musics-social-feature-connect-doesnt-look-bright/#6f816105542a|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 相关争议 ==
=== 版税支付争议 ===
苹果公司起初制定的政策中，前三个月的免费试用期内将不向歌手、詞曲作家和音樂製作人支付版税。2015年6月21日，美國創作歌手[[泰勒·斯威夫特|泰勒·斯威夫特]]发表公开信，批评{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的版税支付方法，同时宣布拒绝向{{lang|en|Apple Music}}提供她自己的专辑《[[1989_(泰勒·斯威夫特专辑)|1989]]》。她批评苹果公司的这一政策“不公平”，“令人震惊、失望”，“完全不像这家曾经进步、慷慨的公司应有的做法”。她强调这一做法会给辛苦打拼的新人、词曲作家及音樂製作人造成巨大伤害。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://taylorswift.tumblr.com/post/122071902085/to-apple-love-taylor|title=Taylor Swift - To Apple, Love Taylor|last=Swift|first=Taylor|publisher=Tumblr|date=June 21, 2015|accessdate=June 22, 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701075135/http://taylorswift.tumblr.com/post/122071902085/to-apple-love-taylor|archivedate=2015年7月1日}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/3940500/apple-music-taylor-swift-release/|title=How Taylor Swift Saved Apple Music|work=Time|date=2015-06-30|accessdate=2015-07-19|first=Tim|last=Bajarin|archive-date=2015-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722011420/http://time.com/3940500/apple-music-taylor-swift-release/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-33216778|title=Taylor Swift pulls 1989 album from Apple Music|accessdate=2015-07-19|date=2015-06-21|publisher=BBC News|archive-date=2015-07-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150730105738/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-33216778|dead-url=no}}</ref>独立歌手也指责苹果公司的这一做法。英国独立唱片公司{{le|Beggars Group|Beggars Group}}也同時對这一政策提出不满和批评，认为苹果公司吸引-{}-用户的成本不应当由音乐版权方和歌手支付<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beggars.com/group/pressrelease/90/with-regards-to-apple-music|title=With regards to Apple Music...|accessdate=2015-07-19|publisher=Beggars Group|archive-date=2015-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620063730/http://beggars.com/group/pressrelease/90/with-regards-to-apple-music|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":2" />。

在斯威夫特发表公开信的第二天，苹果公司副总裁{{le|艾迪·柯尔|Eddy Cue}}在{{lang|en|[[Twitter|Twitter]]}}上作出回应，表示听到了斯威夫特和独立音樂人的呼吁。同时他宣布修改{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的版税支付政策，在试用期也同样会为歌手、詞曲作家及音樂製作人支付报酬，用户则仍然可以免费试用。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-33220189|title=Apple Music changes policy after Taylor Swift stand|publisher=BBC News|date=2015-06-22|accessdate=2015-07-19|archive-date=2015-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709153915/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-33220189|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6605568/apple-changes-course-after-taylor-swift-open-letter-will-pay-labels-during|title=Apple Changes Course After Taylor Swift Open Letter: Will Pay Labels During Free Trial|last=Halperin|first=Shirley|work=[[告示牌_(雜誌)|Billboard]]|date=2015-06-21|accessdate=2015-07-19|archive-date=2015-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150622065723/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6605568/apple-changes-course-after-taylor-swift-open-letter-will-pay-labels-during|dead-url=no}}</ref>斯威夫特随后则通过{{lang|en|Twitter}}表示经历这一事件之后，乐意将专辑《1989》发布到{{lang|en|Apple Music}}。她同时表示并非与苹果公司签订独家协议，并称这是自己第一次感觉把自己的专辑发布到流媒体服务是正确的做法。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/06/25/taylor-swift-1989-apple-music|title=Taylor Swift is putting 1989 on Apple Music|last=Rosen|first=Christopher|work=[[Entertainment_Weekly|Entertainment Weekly]]|date=2015-06-25|accessdate=2015-07-19|archive-date=2015-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626164203/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/06/25/taylor-swift-1989-apple-music|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 涉嫌不当竞争 ===
2015年7月，[[美国聯邦貿易委員會|美国聯邦貿易委員會]]对苹果公司展开调查，其原因是{{lang|en|Apple Music}}等服务涉嫌不当竞争。[[明尼苏达州|明尼苏达州]][[民主党_(美国)|民主党籍]][[美国参议院|联邦参议员]][[艾尔·弗兰肯|艾尔·弗兰肯]]也向[[美国司法部|司法部]]提出建议，要求对苹果公司及{{lang|en|Apple Music}}服务涉嫌不当竞争一案展开深入调查。<ref name="variety">{{cite web|url=http://variety.com/2015/digital/news/apple-music-under-investigation-over-app-store-tax-1201546263/|title=Apple Music Under Investigation Over App Store 'Tax'|work=Variety|date=2015-07-22|accessdate=2015-07-24|first=Janko|last=Roettgers|archive-date=2015-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150724000632/http://variety.com/2015/digital/news/apple-music-under-investigation-over-app-store-tax-1201546263/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Verge: FTC">{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/7/21/9009881/apple-ftc-investigation-music-streaming-30-percent-tax|title=FTC investigation into Apple heats up, music streaming services hit with subpoenas|accessdate=2015-07-24|date=2015-07-21|last=Singleton|first=Micah|work=The Verge|archive-date=2015-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150724010911/http://www.theverge.com/2015/7/21/9009881/apple-ftc-investigation-music-streaming-30-percent-tax|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Verge: Al">{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/7/22/9016449/al-franken-letter-government-apple-music|title=Al Franken asks for Apple Music investigation that's already happening|accessdate=2015-07-24|date=2015-07-22|last=Cox|first=Jamieson|work=The Verge|archive-date=2015-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150723160544/http://www.theverge.com/2015/7/22/9016449/al-franken-letter-government-apple-music|dead-url=no}}</ref>苹果公司的政策要求其平台上的应用程序必须使用特定的[[应用程序接口|应用程序接口]]出售程序中的产品和服务，同时从中收取30%的费用，因此其平台上的[[Spotify|Spotify]]、{{le|Rdio|Rdio}}、{{le|Rhapsody (在线音乐服务)|Rhapsody (online music service)|Rhapsody}}和[[Tidal|Tidal]]等其他音乐流媒体软件不得不提高iOS平台的订阅价格以补偿这一额外成本；苹果公司亦不允许这些软件将用户引导至相应网站以更低廉的价格购买这些产品或服务<ref name="Verge: FTC"/><ref name="Verge: rival">{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/5/6/8558647/apple-ftc-spotify-app-store-antitrust|title=Rival music services say Apple's App Store pricing is anticompetitive|accessdate=2015-07-24|date=2015-05-06|last=Singleton|first=Micah|work=The Verge|archive-date=2015-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150724210948/http://www.theverge.com/2015/5/6/8558647/apple-ftc-spotify-app-store-antitrust|dead-url=no}}</ref>。与之相反，{{lang|en|Apple Music}}则不受此类限制的影响，没有额外成本，无须提高订阅价格<ref name="Verge: FTC"/>。此外，苹果公司禁止其平台上类似的音乐流媒体服务进行免费促销，也禁止提供家庭用户计划；而{{lang|en|Apple Music}}却在前三个月免费提供服务，也推出了家庭用户的付费方案<ref name="Verge: FTC"/>。而在{{lang|en|Apple Music}}推出之前，苹果公司也已经向多家[[唱片公司|唱片公司]]施压，要求其停止与{{lang|en|Spotify}}等免费流媒体服务合作，以减少{{lang|en|Apple Music}}未来遇到的竞争。此种行为已经引起联邦贸易委员会和[[美国司法部|司法部]]的关注。<ref name="Verge: rival"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/5/4/8540935/apple-labels-spotify-streaming|title=Apple pushing music labels to kill free Spotify streaming ahead of Beats relaunch|work=The Verge|date=2015-05-04|accessdate=2015-07-24|first=Micah|last=Singleton|archive-date=2015-07-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721132831/http://www.theverge.com/2015/5/4/8540935/apple-labels-spotify-streaming|dead-url=no}}</ref>类似涉嫌不当竞争的诸多做法引发了竞争对手的极大不满，甚至有业内人士评价称：“像苹果这样的公司，吃着自己的蛋糕，还要抢走其他所有人的蛋糕来吃，实在是荒唐。”<ref name="Verge: FTC"/>2016年6月，美国[[马萨诸塞州|马萨诸塞州]]民主党籍联邦参议员[[伊丽莎白·华伦|伊丽莎白·华伦]]在[[华盛顿特区|华盛顿特区]]发表演讲，其中公开指责了苹果公司和{{lang|en|Apple Music}}的垄断服务，称联邦贸易委员会的调查仍在进行中，委员会正在研究是否起诉苹果公司违反美国[[反垄断法|反托拉斯法]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/7423881/elizabeth-warren-speech-apple-google-amazon-antitrust-competition|title=Elizabeth Warren Hits Apple Music's 'Treatment' of Rivals|work=Billboard|date=2016-06-30|accessdate=2016-07-11|first=Marc|last=Schneider|archive-date=2016-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160705172017/http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/7423881/elizabeth-warren-speech-apple-google-amazon-antitrust-competition|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://fortune.com/2016/06/30/elizabeth-warren-apple-google/|title=Elizabeth Warren Says Apple and Google 'Snuff Out Competition'|work=Fortune|date=2016-06-30|accessdate=2016-07-11|first=Don|last=Reisinger|archive-date=2016-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160704131313/http://fortune.com/2016/06/30/elizabeth-warren-apple-google/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

